### 4. Colossus of the Drylands
**Complexity**: High
**Setting**: Desert wasteland with giant monsters (Shadow of the Colossus inspired)

**Core Concept**: Hunt massive Colossus creatures across the Drylands to prevent the rise of Kudamat.

**Colossus Mechanics**:
Colossi are built with multiple **Segments** (Head, Body, Limbs, etc.):
- Each segment has: Adjacent Segments, Difficulty, HP, Attack stats
- Segments can have special features (Fatal, Armored, Cascade, etc.)
- PCs must climb on and attack specific segments
- Some segments immune to damage except from specific ranges

**Example Colossus - Kelir, The Virulent Hate**:
- Size: 275 ft. tall, 150 ft. wide
- Segments: 1 Head, 1 Shell, 1 Body Cavity, 2 Claws, 4 Legs
- Thresholds: 30/65 | Stress: 6
- Features include: Brood Attack, Swatting Pests, Colossal Power
- Fatal segment (Body Cavity) defeats Kelir when destroyed

**Kudamat Emergence Tracker**:
- **Siphoning Track**: Marks when PCs rest (1 for short, 2 for long rest)
- **Kudamat's Power**: Starts at 0, increases with d12 rolls when track fills or colossus dies
- When all 9 colossi slain OR Power reaches 100, Kudamat emerges
- Kudamat's Severe threshold = Power value; Major threshold = half (rounded up)

**Leveling**: PCs level up immediately upon defeating each colossus (reach level 10 after all nine)

